note.p: NLS Adv. 72.1.2 is a large and diverse manuscript associated with the Beaton family. While it contains a large number of medical texts, other fields of learning, such as logic and cosmology, are also well-represented. Furthermore, some of the medical items are unusual, compared to what is available from other manuscripts. A selection of of texts from the manuscript is presented here, with opportunities to transcribe material on otherwise poorly represented subjects being given priority.
